# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Career.AI Next.js application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in `package.json`
- Updated `package-lock.json` to reflect the new dependency

### 2. Analytics Component Integration
Modified `src/app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the ThemeProvider and AuthProvider wrappers
- Placement ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages while maintaining existing context providers

### 3. Implementation Details
Following the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router:
- Used the framework-specific import path: `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Positioned the Analytics component at the root layout level for site-wide tracking
- Preserved existing code structure, fonts, metadata, and context providers

## Files Modified
- `career-app/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `career-app/package-lock.json` - Updated lockfile with new package
- `career-app/src/app/layout.tsx` - Integrated Analytics component

## Verification
- Linter check: No new errors introduced in layout.tsx
- Code structure: Maintains existing patterns and conventions
- TypeScript: No type errors in the Analytics implementation

## Next Steps
Once deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
2. Visit the deployed site to generate analytics events
3. Verify tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

## Notes
- The Analytics component will only send data when deployed to Vercel
- No configuration is needed for basic page view tracking
- The implementation follows Next.js App Router best practices
- Build failed during testing due to pre-existing Firebase configuration issues (unrelated to Analytics)
